  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Study 22003, &quot;An Open-Label, Flexible-Dose Evaluation of the Safety and Tolerability of
      STX209 for Treatment of Irritability in Subjects With Autism Spectrum Disorders(ASD)&quot;
      currently is evaluating the efficacy of STX209 (R-baclofen) for management of typical problem
      behaviors, such as irritability and aggression, in subjects with ASD. This study (22007) will
      enter subjects who complete Study 22003 into a long-term, open-label study.The open-label
      extension protocol will provide necessary data on the long-term safety and tolerability of
      STX209 among subjects with ASD who receive treatment under conditions more closely reflective
      of their general medical care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
